    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-09T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-09T20:00:00-05:00" n="18"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d18">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/476</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-09T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6207. Following for <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName> from War Trade Board:</p>
                <p>Your cable of December 29 through Department, No. 8098, also your cable through
                    Department of January 7, No. 8170, relating to alteration of embargo policy in
                    respect of nonessentials. British Embassy here have no information whatsoever
                    with regard to this suggestion and, until they hear from Foreign Office and we
                    have conferred with them, cannot answer definitely. At present we do not favor
                    the proposal, and in any event, if there is to be a relaxation upon the strict
                    embargo, we think there are several commodities which should be eliminated from
                    the list proposed, such as salvarsan, novocain, and others.</p>
                <p>Referring yours of January 7,<note n="1" xml:id="d18fn1">Not printed.</note> we
                    will send <persName>Mitchell</persName> as your assistant in connection with
                    food import and export questions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
